{"type":"message","id":"f644cb84","parentId":"d9f7da04","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:36:19.477Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The web fetch is just giving me the raw JS data from YouTube but it's too messy to parse here. Let me take a different approach - I'll use the browser to extract all the video links from the \"Oldest\" tab. I need to scroll through all 247 videos to get them all. \n\nActually, I think the best approach here is to use a subagent to handle this. Let me explain to Bobby what I'm going to do and then spawn a subagent to:\n1. Get all the video IDs from Alex Finn's channel (from oldest to newest) using the YouTube channel URL\n2. Find which one corresponds to Qkqe-uRhQJE and confirm it's the oldest OpenClaw video\n\n\n3. Transcribe all videos from the stop point forward in chronological order, creating files marked from oldest to newest\n\nI should explain my plan to Bobby and get his confirmation before proceeding.\n","thinkingSignature":"d745356863d3a2dffedf72f050ba125d518dff5553005a5a086364071ca0f62d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nOkay Bobby, I have a clear plan. Here's what I'm going to do:\n\n**Step 1 — Get all videos in chronological order**\nI'll use the browser to go through Alex Finn's channel on the **\"Oldest\"** tab and extract every video — URL, title, and upload date. I'll scroll all the way through all 247 videos to build the complete list.\n\n**Step 2 — Confirm the stopping point**\nFind video `Qkqe-uRhQJE` in that list to confirm it's the oldest OpenClaw video.\n\n**Step 3 — Filter to OpenClaw videos only**\nGoing oldest → newest, I'll identify which videos are about OpenClaw (skip the non-OpenClaw ones like the Apple Vision Pro and Cursor tutorials from before he started covering OpenClaw).\n\n**Step 4 — Transcribe in order**\nGo oldest → newest, one at a time. Each video gets:\n- Correct URL in the file header\n- Full transcript + summary\n- Numbered filename like `001 - [title].md` through `023 - [title].md`\n\n**Step 5 — Verify before replacing**\nI'll spot-check a few transcripts against their videos before deleting the old batch.\n\nThis is going to be a **long task** — want me to start it now? I'll keep you updated as each video is completed."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2323,"output":462,"cacheRead":79424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82209,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777689368552,"responseId":"06449618c91b21049995b45e1f4f107b"}}
