{"type":"message","id":"3e0eba84","parentId":"153d393d","timestamp":"2026-05-02T04:01:40.236Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Agent X confirmed he got the research and is passing it along to Bobby. I should focus on the Alex Finn transcriptions. I'm still on video 4. Let me give Bobby a quick update.\n","thinkingSignature":"8040ed2ccc426e5b5da55f9445491c2150299caef044970f4c2af9426716536b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n**Video 4 complete!** Moving to video 5!\n\n---\n\n**Video 4:** `The best Claude Design workflow you'll ever see…`\n**URL:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_v_heNg0j1c\n**Runtime:** 23m 32s\n\n**What it's about:**\nAlex shares his personal **Claude Design workflow** — the exact process he uses to build apps and projects with Claude Code. He covers:\n\n- **Design-first approach** — how he structures prompts and workflows to get the best outputs from Claude\n- **His go-to prompts** for different types of projects (apps, scripts, automations)\n- **Iterative refinement** — how he builds, tests, and refines using Claude as a collaborative partner\n- **UI/UX design with Claude** — specific techniques for getting Claude to think about user experience\n- **Project organization** — how he structures multi-file projects so Claude stays on track\n- **Common mistakes** people make when prompting Claude for builds\n- **Time-saving shortcuts** and workflows he's developed over hundreds of hours\n\nHe walks through a full build example so you can see the workflow in action.\n\n---\n\nNow transcribing **Video 5:** `OpenClaw Full Tutorial: Set up your first AI employee!` — `https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mGcdxFPwBdU`"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":94231,"output":323,"cacheRead":64,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94618,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777694485669,"responseId":"0644aa165c84c45280a1