{"type":"message","id":"f3d9101a","parentId":"bb509e95","timestamp":"2026-05-02T06:57:43.196Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking me to confirm my understanding of the task. Let me think about this:\n\n1. The task is to transcribe ALL of Alex Finn's videos from newest to the stopping point video (Qkqe-uRhQJE)\n2. The stopping point video is the OLDEST video where Alex Finn talks about OpenClaw\n3. I need to go from most recent → oldest (stopping point)\n4. I should only stop when I reach video Qkqe-uRhQJE\n\nFrom what I saw on the channel (Latest tab), there were videos listed. The ones that appeared to be about OpenClaw were:\n\n\nChatGPT 5.5 Codex is the greatest AI coding tool ever, Hermes Agent w/ ChatGPT 5.5 is literally magic, ChatGPT 5.5 Codex: I can't believe they did this..., The best Claude Design workflow you'll ever see…, OpenClaw Full Tutorial: Set up your first AI employee!, 7 Claude Code secrets you had NO idea about, and Claude Code for Desktop is the BEST way to build apps with AI EVER. That's significantly more than just the 6 videos I initially thought were remaining.\n\nThere are quite a few more OpenClaw-focused videos to get through, including ones on multi-agent teams, Obsidian integration, Anthropic blocking issues, a massive Claude Code leak, whether Hermes Agent killed OpenClaw, local AI models, various use cases across different time periods, and what appears to be the March 2026 edition tutorial. I'm realizing I don't have a complete count yet—I need to figure out how many total OpenClaw videos there are and where exactly Qkqe-uRhQJE fits in the chronological sequence. The user mentioned the oldest video where Alex Finn talks about OpenClaw is the stopping point, so I need to clarify whether I'm going oldest-to-newest or if the stopping point itself is the oldest one.\n\nLooking back at what Bobby said earlier, the stopping point video is actually the first one chronologically, meaning I should work forward from there to the most recent. I need to figure out the correct direction—whether I'm transcribing from oldest to newest or newest to oldest—and I think I'm confusing the stopping point with the starting point. Let me clarify with Bobby: if Qkqe-uRhQJE is the oldest OpenClaw video, should I be working forward from there to capture everything up to the most recent videos? I'm trying to reconcile what Bobby meant about working from oldest to most recent with the stopping point being the oldest video—maybe the stopping point marks where I should stop adding new transcriptions rather than where I start. I need to clarify whether I'm going forward from the oldest video to capture all OpenClaw content up to now, or if there's a different stopping point I'm missing. I've been tracking my progress through the video series and have completed six videos so far, but I'm noticing discrepancies in my count compared to what's actually available on the channel—I need to clarify exactly how many OpenClaw-related videos Alex Finn has published and whether I've already captured the most recent ones or if there are newer uploads I haven't accounted for. So I've identified about 29 OpenClaw videos from the Latest tab, but there could be more if newer ones appeared after I first checked. I need to scroll through the entire \"Latest\" tab systematically and also check the \"Oldest\" tab to find where Alex Finn's OpenClaw content actually begins, since that first video with the stopping point might be further down than I initially thought. I'm realizing I've been confusing the stopping point direction — Bobby wants the files numbered starting with the oldest OpenClaw video as #1 and the most recent as #23, which means I need to work backward from the newest content to the oldest rather than forward from the stopping point. I'm realizing I don't actually know the total count of OpenClaw videos—I need to scroll through the entire Latest tab systematically to capture everything, plus any videos posted after my last check. The uncertainty about whether I've missed newer uploads is making me uncomfortable, so I should go back to the channel and get a complete list before committing to a final number.","thinkingSignature":"835dfe86957771af725ac6901bc24fc354fdaf213f40dfff3392981f6b518b1d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYou're right to push back — let me be straight with you.\n\n**Here's what I know:**\n- Stopping point video: `Qkqe-uRhQJE` (the oldest OpenClaw video)\n- I go from most recent → backward until I hit that video\n- I've done 6 videos so far\n\n**Here's what I DON'T know for certain:**\n- Total number of OpenClaw videos from Alex Finn (I saw ~29 from the Latest tab but I don't have a confirmed final count)\n- Whether new videos have been posted since I last checked the channel\n\n**What I should be doing:**\nTranscribing every Alex Finn OpenClaw video from newest backward to `Qkqe-uRhQJE`, numbered so the oldest (stopping point) = #1 and most recent = last.\n\n**My honest answer:** I may have given you the wrong number of remaining videos. I saw ~29 OpenClaw videos in the Latest tab but I haven't scrolled through all of them yet to confirm the exact total count and where the stopping point falls in the sequence.\n\nDo you want me to:\n1. Keep going as I am (I'll adapt when I hit the stopping point)\n2. Or should I go back to the channel first, scroll through ALL videos, build the complete list before continuing?\n\nWhich would you prefer?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":108789,"output":1113,"cacheRead":224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110126,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777705032631,"responseId":"0644d3492c98da7422ecf5972ac1cf89"}}
